    <sectiondef kind="typedef">
      <memberdef kind="typedef" id="expected__MR__TeethMaskToDirectionVolumeConvertor__std__string_8h_1aa30b1977d5827fa4332728b958ee1381" prot="public" static="no">
        <type>struct <ref refid="expected__MR__TeethMaskToDirectionVolumeConvertor__std__string_8h_1aa30b1977d5827fa4332728b958ee1381" kindref="member">MR_TeethMaskToDirectionVolumeConvertor</ref></type>
        <definition>typedef struct MR_TeethMaskToDirectionVolumeConvertor MR_TeethMaskToDirectionVolumeConvertor</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>MR_TeethMaskToDirectionVolumeConvertor</name>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This class is an alternative to directly invoking meshToDirectionVolume for the mesh retrieved from the teeth mask. It is better because when a single mesh is created from mask, some neighboring teeth might fuse together, creating incorrect mask. This class invokes meshing for each teeth separately, thus eliminating this problem. Generated from class <computeroutput>MR::TeethMaskToDirectionVolumeConvertor</computeroutput>. Supported <computeroutput><ref refid="common_8h_1ac983b89bddb9b22c9b416f31399f0095" kindref="member">MR_PassBy</ref></computeroutput> modes: <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_Copy</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_Move</computeroutput> (and <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_DefaultArgument</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_NoObject</computeroutput> if supported by the callee). </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
